     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d031n1-ptr" id="PJA08d031n1">1</a>
      <p>These were letters from Arthur Middleton of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-03-0001-0145" class="document">4</a> July (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>) and Edward Rutledge of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-06-02-0229" class="document">16</a> July 1778 (vol. 6:294295). For Gillon and his activities, see the Rutledge letter, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-06-02-0229&amp;expandNote=PJA06d261n1#PJA06d261n1" class="document">note 1</a>.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d031n2-ptr" id="PJA08d031n2">2</a>
      <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s reply of the 24th has not been found, but see <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to Arthur Middleton, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0033" class="document">24 April</a> (below).</p>
